Frequently Asked Questions

Have questions? We've got answers.

What is a sales funnel?

Website sales funnels are a series of web pages that visitors navigate through with the goal of completing a desired action, like making a purchase or filling out a form. To make sure visitors complete the desired action, the website funnel guides them smoothly and intuitively through the process.

You can also use website funnels to upsell and cross-sell.

Upselling is when you offer a more expensive version of a product or service that the customer already wants. For example, if a customer wants to buy a basic version of a software, the website can offer them an upgraded version with more features.

Cross-selling is when you offer customers related products or services on top of the ones they already want. If a customer is thinking about buying a camera, the site can suggest additional accessories like a tripod or a case.

Using upselling and cross-selling techniques on a website funnel can increase a customer's average purchase value and increase their chances of making multiple purchases. Thus increasing the customer lifetime value.

What is Lifetime Value (LTV)?

Lifetime Value (LTV) is a way for businesses to estimate how much money a customer is likely to spend over the course of their relationship with the company. It's like a score that helps the business understand how valuable a customer is and allows them to make decisions about how to keep them happy and coming back.

Why should I care about LTV?

If you can increase your LTV, it can transform your entire campaign. If you make more money from each customer you can then afford to pay more to acquire new customers. When you increase your bids, you also increase the position of your ads, which then increases the number of clicks you get. More clicks means more opportunities to convert! Thus growing your business as a result!
